@endnode


@node Description "Description"

	This program takes a TTL number and tells you the function of the
	TTL circuit with this number. It do so by using requesters.

@endnode


@node Requirements "Requirements"
	This program requires kickstart v2.x or higher to run, and it also
	requires reqtools.library to be available in your system.
	reqtools.library is *NOT* included in this archive but is widely
	available and shouldn't be hard to find if you don't already have
	this library.
@endnode


@node Installation "Installation"

	If reqtools.library is not installed in your system, then get this
	from your favorite PD source and follow the installation directions
	from the reqtools package.
	It should now be possible to run TTL from where ever you decide to
	put it.
	The program is "pure" and reentrant so if the pure bit is not set
	do I suggest that you set it with the C:Protect command so you
	can 'resident' it.

@endnode


@node Usage "Usage"

	Just double click on its icon, or start it from CLI and answer the requesters.
	Accepts the argument or workbench tooltype PUBSCREEN=<Public screen name>,
	with which you can define which screen you want TTL to appear upon.

@endnode


@node Bugs "Bugs"

	No known @{"bugs" link bugdefinition }, but if you find any please report them to
	the @{"author" link Author}. Please make clear what's wrong and tell me what you
